1
00:00:02,050 --> 00:00:04,145
卡门飓风昨天过境
Hurricane Carmen came through here yesterday,

2
00:00:04,278 --> 00:00:06,075
沿途几乎摧毁了一切
destroying nearly everything in its path.

3
00:00:06,148 --> 00:00:09,083
沿海的其他城镇也一样
And as in other towns up and down the coast,

4
00:00:09,151 --> 00:00:11,949
拉巴特湾的捕虾业
Bayou La Batre's entire shrimping industry

5
00:00:12,021 --> 00:00:14,353
成为卡门飓风的最大受害者
has fallen victim to Carmen

6
00:00:14,424 --> 00:00:17,257
渔港完全成了废墟
and has been left in utter ruin.

7
00:00:17,326 --> 00:00:18,759
记者被告知
This reporter has learned,

8
00:00:18,829 --> 00:00:21,263
实际上只有一条捕虾船
in fact, only one shrimping boat

9
00:00:21,331 --> 00:00:22,855
幸免于难
actually survived the storm.

10
00:00:22,933 --> 00:00:25,401
露西 露西 福雷斯来了
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

11
00:00:25,470 --> 00:00:28,564
从此以后 捕虾就很容易了
After that, shrimping was easy.

12
00:00:28,640 --> 00:00:31,404
“将会有丰厚的回报”
# There will be great bounty #

13
00:00:31,477 --> 00:00:34,139
“我的上帝…”
# Oh, my God... #

14
00:00:34,213 --> 00:00:36,147
因为人们仍然需要虾
Since people still needed them shrimps

15
00:00:36,216 --> 00:00:38,582
来做虾串烧和虾烧烤什么的
for shrimp cocktails and barbecues and all

16
00:00:38,652 --> 00:00:41,587
而我们的船是唯一剩下的了
and we were the only boat left standing,

17
00:00:41,655 --> 00:00:44,089
他们只能来布巴甘这里买虾
Bubba Gump shrimp's what they got.

18
00:00:44,158 --> 00:00:47,093
我们购置了一大堆船
We got a whole bunch of boats.

19
00:00:47,161 --> 00:00:49,095
有12条珍妮号 还有一个大仓库
12 Jennys, big old warehouse.

20
00:00:49,164 --> 00:00:51,098
我们还订做了帽子
We even have hats

21
00:00:51,166 --> 00:00:53,600
上面写着“布巴甘”
that say "Bubba Gump" on them.

22
00:00:53,669 --> 00:00:55,102
布巴甘捕虾公司
Bubba Gump Shrimp.

23
00:00:55,171 --> 00:00:56,604
这名字家喻户晓
It's a household name.

24
00:00:56,673 --> 00:00:58,334
等等 小兄弟
Hold on there, boy.

25
00:00:58,408 --> 00:01:00,842
你是说你就是…
Are you telling me you're the owner

26
00:01:00,911 --> 00:01:03,141
布巴捕虾公司的老板？
of the Bubba Gump Shrimp Corporation?

27
00:01:03,214 --> 00:01:06,149
对 我们挣了一大堆钱
Yes. We got more money than Davy Crockett.

28
00:01:06,218 --> 00:01:09,153
孩子 我听过很多牛皮
Boy, I heard some whoppers in my time,

29
00:01:09,221 --> 00:01:12,156
这是最大的一个
but that tops them all.

30
00:01:14,260 --> 00:01:17,661
我们身边正坐着一个百万富翁
We were sitting next to a millionaire .

